      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Add your <strong>butternut squash cubes </strong>to a heatproof bowl</p><p>Cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until the squash cubes are fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1654617926120-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1654617926120-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1654617926120-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1654617926120-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1654617926120-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>into rounds</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>– this is your <strong>quick-pickled shallot</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1654617926759-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1654617926759-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1654617926759-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1654617926759-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1654617926759-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Line a baking tray with <strong>baking paper</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half </strong>of the<strong> drained chickpeas </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to one side of the baking tray with a drizzle of<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for an initial 10 min or until starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1654617936228-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1654617936228-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1654617936228-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1654617936228-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1654617936228-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the squash is fork-tender, season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth</p><p>Add your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>garam masala </strong>and the <strong>remaining chickpeas </strong>and roughly mash – this is your <strong>spiced squash mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1654617944032-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1654617944032-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1654617944032-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1654617944032-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1654617944032-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>spiced squash mixture</strong> into 2 per person,<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>shape into sausage-shaped kebabs and insert a <strong>skewer </strong>into each – these are your <strong>kebabs</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to a plate with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Roll the <strong>kebabs</strong> in the <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> until fully coated – these are your <strong>coated kebabs</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1654617953952-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1654617953952-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1654617953952-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1654617953952-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1654617953952-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After the chickpeas have had an initial 10 min, add the <strong>coated kebabs </strong>to the other side of the tray<strong> </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Return the tray to the oven for a further 10-15 min or until everything is golden and crispy – these are your <strong>spiced squash & chickpea seekh kebabs </strong>and <strong>crispy chickpeas</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1654617965836-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1654617965836-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1654617965836-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1654617965836-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1654617965836-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>green tomato chutney </strong>and<strong> chopped coriander </strong>in a bowl with your <strong>mayo</strong> and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water </strong>– this is your <strong>sauce</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>When everything is almost ready, add your<strong> rotis</strong> to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 2-3 min or until warm</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1654617994416-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1654617994416-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1654617994416-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1654617994416-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1654617994416-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, fill the <strong>warmed</strong> <strong>rotis </strong>with the <strong>sliced tomato</strong>,<strong> salad </strong>and <strong>spiced squash & chickpea seekh kebabs</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>crispy chickpeas </strong>and <strong>quick-pickled shallot</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the<strong> sauce</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
